=Discussion=

Chelsea Robinson, from the book, [[Assets in Common]]:

"Aggregating assets into unifying entities like holding companies or multi-stakeholder cooperatives. Achieving this via typical structures can be a slippery slope to monopoly and cartel behavior.

However, when designed with shared ownership and stewardship, these can create value for stakeholders and long-term missions. Conscious consolidation can help with efficiency gains and greater influence in the market."

(https://wiki.p2pfoundation.net/Assets_in_Common)

